00:42:05.200 --> 00:42:10.000
means "I surrender myself to the enlightened one"

00:42:10.240 --> 00:42:12.799
"Buddham sharanam gacchami."

00:42:12.999 --> 00:42:16.280
Then they say, "Dharmam sharanam gacchami."

00:42:16.520 --> 00:42:19.720
"Dharmam" is that valency business I'm talking about,

00:42:19.960 --> 00:42:24.999
that "I surrender myself to my valencies, my dharma" - dharma.

00:42:25.440 --> 00:42:29.240
And the third one He said is, "Sangam sharanam gacchami."

00:42:29.480 --> 00:42:32.920
That means, "I surrender myself to collectivity".

00:42:33.400 --> 00:42:34.840
Is Sahaja Yoga only,

00:42:35.040 --> 00:42:38.280
but you should be able to see between the lines.

00:42:39.999 --> 00:42:41.960
Same about Gita.

00:42:42.160 --> 00:42:45.640
If you read Gita superficially,

00:42:45.880 --> 00:42:48.760
you will think that He has said about karma yoga

00:42:48.999 --> 00:42:50.800
and He has said about gyana yoga.

00:42:51.000 --> 00:42:54.320
Now what gyana yoga is, what I'm talking about,

00:42:54.560 --> 00:42:57.960
that you have to know it on your central nervous system.

00:42:58.640 --> 00:43:01.720
But Krishna didn't talk much about it.

00:43:01.999 --> 00:43:05.520
So then Arjuna asked, "What about the karma?"

00:43:05.960 --> 00:43:10.400
So Krishna was a incarnation of diplomacy, I must say,

00:43:10.640 --> 00:43:12.120
divine diplomacy,

00:43:12.360 --> 00:43:14.680
because He knew about the human brain,

00:43:14.920 --> 00:43:17.360
and He knew how to put it forward.

00:43:17.640 --> 00:43:21.400
So He said, "All right, you do all your karmas,

00:43:21.680 --> 00:43:25.280
and put it at the Lotus Feet of the Lord",

00:43:25.560 --> 00:43:28.480
which cannot be, it's not possible.

00:43:28.720 --> 00:43:31.080
We may mentally think, "Oh, I'm doing all for God's sake.

00:43:31.320 --> 00:43:33.640
I'm doing this." That's just our imagination.

00:43:33.880 --> 00:43:37.720
But you just don't do it, because the karma has to become akarma,

00:43:37.999 --> 00:43:39.960
means "non-action".

00:43:40.160 --> 00:43:43.280
That's only possible when you get your Self-Realization.

00:43:43.720 --> 00:43:46.640
When a Self-realized soul gives you Kundalini, he doesn't say,

00:43:46.920 --> 00:43:48.799
raises your Kundalini, doesn't say, "I do it".

00:43:48.999 --> 00:43:52.280
He says, "It's rising, it's going, it's working out."

00:43:52.520 --> 00:43:54.280
In the third person he talks,

00:43:54.560 --> 00:43:57.240
so the whole thing becomes akarma.

00:43:57.480 --> 00:43:59.840
