01:09:40.280 --> 01:09:43.960
I'll quote a beautiful poem written by

01:09:44.160 --> 01:09:48.999
one very famous poet, Namadeva, who was just a tailor,

01:09:49.640 --> 01:09:51.880
and was very much appreciated by Nanaka,

01:09:52.080 --> 01:09:54.680
and he said that "Now you better write in Punjabi language".

01:09:54.920 --> 01:09:58.799
So he wrote such a big book of things in Punjabi language,

01:09:58.999 --> 01:10:01.440
and is used in the Guru Granth Sahib.

01:10:01.680 --> 01:10:04.480
He was a poet from Maharashtra.

01:10:04.760 --> 01:10:07.799
So one day he went to see another realized soul,

01:10:07.999 --> 01:10:10.880
who was a potter.

01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:12.799
